Ok, I&quot;ve *USED THESE PETS ON TEST*, ok?<br>
Right: they suck suck SUCK for sustained damage, guess I should do a log and post it. They have *NPC* AI, they will occasionally IC/Draught of Fire the hell out of a mob, blast it to bits...then spend next three mobs meleeing and rooting/snaring. It's extremely random. As a mage I find them hysterically funny, but, beside fun factor, on a raid they would *BLOW GOATS*.<br>
<br>
1) Root is bad, indescribably bad on a pet at higher lvls, its nice soloing with a true earth pet, but in a group or raid...do I need to say how *** up a pet would be casting high lvl wiz roots, hm? :/ And solo I need DEPENEDABLE roots, that an earth pet casts continually every few ticks *guaranteed*.<br>
<br>
2) mages want a *sustainably damaging pet*. I don't want to have to p-ss around so I can get it to cast *useful* spells continually, jeez!  Make the blasted pet a *MAGE* so it just casts Char, Shock of Swords and Malosi. NPC mages have restricted spell line ups unlike wizzies: Fire/Magic DD, Debuff, so they dotn root/snare.  If that's ALL it casts, either doing damage or a usefull debuff, wahooo, great!<br>
<br>
3) Fire pets have *CRAP* for hit points, the 62 water has about <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&lt;=</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->3k hp, go test it see how quick it does. Then go check 63 fire..it dies even *faster*, ok? Fire pets can't tank for buttons, that's never what they are used for, up to lvl 49 pet, their huge damage shield is used to let mobs beat themselves to death on them. Unless a pet had a 200+hp Damage Shield it would be no use at high lvl because mobs would flatten the pet in about 10 seconds. The 63 fire pet WITH O'Kiels and its own innate DS that, hurray! it casts again, has a total DS of 67 hp. <br>
  So the 63 pet *cannot be used to tank*. it also melees like crap: 58 hp max damage versus 81 hp of other pets.<br>
<br>
4) Ok example of 2 of those pets killing the Seb Protector: er how many hps does Seb protector have anyway: 20k? if you had two 62 Water Pets on it's back, 90+ DPS (old world mob and pets would have proc weapons, base 70-90 DPS on Tier 2 mobs), they would do 21,600+ hp or so in those TWO MINUTES. See where I am going? Did anyone test the water 62 pets in SAME situation? maybe, perhaps...they'd kill it *faster* hm? <br>
<br>
5) This is decending to kindergarten levels <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
