Also about HP, here's a quote from a mage who used the pet on test.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Cons: Mana pool is itsy bitsy. Runs out of juice quickly. A stiff breeze can still kill it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
I agree, it seems like the idea of IC is what is upsetting to most and I would have no problem if the nuke was replaced.  However, you need to keep in mind that this would be a lvl63 spell summoning a lvl60 pet that could cast a lvl49 spell.  Now more than likely this lvl63 mage is going to be raiding and hunting against 60+ mobs and I don't know about anyone else but I get enough resists using lvl 60 spells in BoT much less trying to land a lvl 49 spell. <br>
<br>
Now if the pet chaincasts IC and Draught of Fire nonstop(which I've never seen a pet or NPC chain cast) it would be putting out ~130dps which I think is too high and should be adjusted.  I have a feeling that when this pet is finally tuned and tested we're going to see it putting out around 80-90dps; this is about the same as the water pet damage output.  <br>
<br>
I know a lot of wizards feel that a pet who casts decent spells will be infringing on the wizard class.  If this pet is putting out the same sort of damage as any other pet, even if it is casting instead of melee, I can't possibly see it as overpowering or infringing on another class. <br>
<br>
The core issue here is that the 50+ fire pets, a supposed wizard pet, are clearly broken and have a damage output that is only a fraction of the other pets.  I think most parses of the 63 fire pet set its damage output at around 30-40dps.  If they add in spells that boost this to 80-90dps, inline with the other 60+ pets, I can't see how this is infringing on any other class.  Yes, at the moment the burst DPS of the 63 fire pet is around 130dps, but I have a feeling as more parses become available we're going to see that between melee and casting other spells its damage output is roughly the same as the rest of the mage pets.  Might the new pet need some tuning, yes; but as a mage I would like to see our 50+ fire pets made useful instead of being a waste of a spellbook slot.<br>
<br>
Falkahnhan<br>
