<br>
Now, great it casts all these nifty spells, let's look at some perks it doesn't get:<br>
<br>
- Can't choose what spells it uses. It just follows a set script and tends to be unpredictable. It might chain cast nukes, it might chain cast snares or roots, you just never know what them crazy elementals will do.<br>
<br>
- It doesn't benefit from focus effects. While you can use spells, songs, and items to increase your spells effectiveness and cost, a pet cannot.<br>
<br>
- Nukes stack well, a nuking pet also doesn't take up a group slot. So nobody is going to go looking for a pet to replace a real wizard. And you will happily conincide together blasting things into small itty bitty bits. It's not like, damn, there's a fire pet here, I CAN'T NUKE!<br>
<br>
- SOE wanted this pet to be a wizard, I dunno why they wanted it to be a wizard, but it is and has been quite awhile. I don't think we're going to sway them from this madness, but we can try to make the best of it. Now saying that, up till now, this pet has been pathetic. What is wrong with making it good ? If anything, the changes they've got listed only put it on par with our other pets and then only temporarily. This actually isn't far enough considering the pet cannot tank while our other pets can (water aint too great, but it'll last awhile if the mob is slowed). But I'll take what improvements I can get.<br>
<br>
The bulk of the arguments I've seen here sum up to: it uses our coolest looking nuke, that is sooooo unfair. That's gotta be the most shallow argument I've heard, especially considering how many folks have their spell effects turned off and messages gagged.<br>
<br>
