<br>
Wizards have supposedly 1 major advantage in nuking--  They can call upon Magic, Fire and Ice.  Of those, only Ice is rare among casters, being mostly the province of Shaman, Druids, and Beastlords.<br>
<br>
Wizards also hold a minor advantage with the ratio's of our spells, which is most pronounced with our Ice Nukes.<br>
<br>
<br>
Giving the Mage pet Ice comet not only gives Mages a valid solution for mobs that are resistant to Magic and Fire spells, but it also does so mana free.<br>
<br>
Observation:<br>
The last thing you want to see is a summoned Mage pet.  Every mage in the game practicaly immediatly summons a pet to help it... with a lucky set of rolls, you'd have the Mage's fire pet, the pet's fire pet, and the pet's pet's fire pet... gah, you think it through...<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Solution:<br>
   Give Mage pets a set spell list that includes only the Fire based spells of wizards.  Let them Cast Draught of Fire, Pillar of Flame, and Tears of Solusk.  Let them also cast the various stuns, Atols(make sure it fizzles alot), and a Skin--leave out root, they have earth pets for this. Replace FireElemental Aura with Okeils. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And for real fun, have it TL the mage randomly and at random intervals....  <p><br>
